  "texts": [
    "(2) Based on the HCL-TAL model, MPC-CA proposes the multi-channels prototypical, multi-channels support contrastive loss, and condition adversarial attacks methods, achieving better results in four few-shot settings on the FewEvent dataset.",
    "Specifically, MPC-CA outperforms HCL-TAT by 0.31%, 1.34%, 1.5%, and 1.82% in the four few-shot settings, respectively, demonstrating the effectiveness of these proposed methods.",
    "(3) Similar to ProAcT, Meta-Event performs well in a 5-way-5-shot and 5-way-10-shot settings, but not well in the 10-way-5-shot and 10-way-10shot settings.",
    "In addition, we found that Meta-Event is unstable on all few-shot settings and has a significant difference in F1 scores under different random seeds, indicating that its robustness is not as good as the model proposed in this paper.",
    "Besides, MPC-CA outperforms Meta-Event by 1.27%, 9.48%, 21.06%, and 29.06% in the four few-shot settings, respectively.MPC-CA achieves the best results, effectively addressing the problem of insufficient prototype representation learning by introducing conditional adversarial attacks."
